text.tspan: Choose one, either bare ESP8266 or the one
that has an USB and a 5V input.
Before making a PCB check PCB footprints that match your components!
Test on a breadboard before making a PCB!
Be aware that shift in register (74HC165N) is a different thing as shift out (74HC595) register. One will work and the other won't.
Buttons should be connected to +3V and button in terminal.
This schematic should work, however double check. If any mistakes are found let me know
